                            <comment id="67504" author="rstoya05-aop" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2011 02:59:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-7984&quot; title=&quot;Allow optional @PathVariable&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-7984&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-7984&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="67521" author="hal10001" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2011 06:41:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Although the issue is a duplicate, can you provide some insight into why this wouldn&apos;t be fixed? SPR 7984 is a feature request with additional complications. I&apos;m just asking that the @PathVariable be null if a pattern match is not found in the request mapping.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="67578" author="rstoya05-aop" created="Mon, 20 Jun 2011 02:12:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Apologies for not leaving any comments here. I did leave comments on the linked issue but I didn&apos;t explain why I consider them duplicate.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@PathVariable results in an exception if the variable is not available. If you rely on this behavior, as is more common, allowing null would cause an unintended side effect in cases where you do want to have it. See the @RequestParam annotation for example, which has a &apos;required&apos; flag and a &apos;defaultValue&apos; making a request parameter optional. So in effect your request amounts to allowing for optional path variables.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See my two recommendations under &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-7984&quot; title=&quot;Allow optional @PathVariable&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-7984&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-7984&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="67588" author="hal10001" created="Mon, 20 Jun 2011 06:18:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the additional feedback Rossen. Much appreciated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
